                <updated>Thu, 30 Nov 2017 19:40:22 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Thu, 30 Nov 2017 19:35:28 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>2.9.1</version>
                                    <fixVersion>2.10.0</fixVersion>
                                    <component>Appenders</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>7</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16215632" author="mikaelstaldal" created="Mon, 23 Oct 2017 18:42:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would quite strange to have a property with name &quot;skipXXX&quot; with default value true. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If we want Jansi to be disabled by default, I would suggest that we rather add another property &quot;enableJansi&quot; with default false. And maybe move it to ConsoleAppender.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16215735" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Mon, 23 Oct 2017 19:52:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So now we would have 2 properties that have opposite meanings? So if one has a default of true and one is false what is the overall default?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16215781" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 23 Oct 2017 20:26:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ARG!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16216188" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Tue, 24 Oct 2017 02:03:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;PatternLayout already has two additional config properties to control ANSI escape codes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;disableAnsi&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;noConsoleNoAnsi&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;From a usability point of view these might have been better on the ConsoleAppender, but from an implementation point of view I can see how things became the way they are. Anyway, for the purpose of this ticket, I won&apos;t add another property and I&apos;ll just focus on requiring explicit configuration to load Jansi.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16216219" author="githubbot" created="Tue, 24 Oct 2017 02:58:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user remkop commented on the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/29&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/29&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    FYI: work on this is now in progress under JIRA ticket &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2087&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2087&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16216233" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 24 Oct 2017 03:14:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 73efe3dcf6787e66177a6485271362c5f989e014 in logging-log4j2&apos;s branch refs/heads/master from rpopma&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=logging-log4j2.git;h=73efe3d&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=logging-log4j2.git;h=73efe3d&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2087&quot; title=&quot;Property log4j.skipJansi should have a default of true&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-2087&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-2087&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Jansi now needs to be enabled explicitly (by setting system property `log4j.skipJansi` to `false`). To avoid causing problems for web applications, Log4j will no longer automatically try to load Jansi without explicit configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16216235" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Tue, 24 Oct 2017 03:15:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged into master.&lt;br/&gt;
Please verify and close.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16217546" author="mikaelstaldal" created="Tue, 24 Oct 2017 19:42:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the Javadoc for &lt;tt&gt;PatternLayout.Builder.withDisableAnsi()&lt;/tt&gt; is incorrect, it doesn&apos;t say that it is always default true on other platforms than Windows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Documentation for the same property in &lt;tt&gt;layouts.xml.vm&lt;/tt&gt; also needs to be updated accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16217558" author="mikaelstaldal" created="Tue, 24 Oct 2017 19:47:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Documentation in &lt;tt&gt;configuration.xml.vm&lt;/tt&gt; should also be updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16273255" author="mikaelstaldal" created="Thu, 30 Nov 2017 19:35:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Need to update documentation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16273256" author="mikaelstaldal" created="Thu, 30 Nov 2017 19:35:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Documentation updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
